@node "intro" "Introduction"
                                 @{b}Introduction@{ub}

TBar is a simple task bar clone.  All it does is show a working clock and
nothing else,Yet!.

I've been using dopus for ages and like using it's startmenus.  I used to
startmenu2 for a while but found it didn't really work well with a graphics
card.  Using the startmenu's in dopus was better for mapping icons etc but
left me without a taskbar and clock.  So i thought why don't i just write
one.

So i did.  It's quite basic but it's good enough for my needs an it looks
quite resonable.

Thanks
@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}

Stick in you Wbstartup drawer and rest the computer.  Thats it.

It has no closier facility as this causes some starnge delays and excessive
cpu load for some reason.

It adjust itself to the screen width and will always be at the bottom of the
screen.

I use cybergrapics and it work so it there will be no problem with a graphics
card.
@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Bugs"
BUgs

1. No wsay of closing it down.

2. Problems when startmenu is moved.  The old image is still imprinted on the
taskbar.  This might have something to do with the window being a background
but i'm not sure.
@endnode

